properties.Name: MedicalTest
properties.Description: A medical test is a diagnostic procedure performed to confirm, or determine the presence of a disease, condition or state in an individual.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Medical Test.

Columns.Name: EncounterId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Encounter with a Service Provider.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Medical Test Type.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestRequestedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the associated test was requested.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestScheduledForTimestamp
Columns.Description: The scheduled timestamp of the medical test.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestStartTimestamp
Columns.Description: The start timestamp of the medical test.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestCompletedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The end or completion timestamp of the test.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestDescription
Columns.Description: A description of the medical test.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestTakenPositionDescription
Columns.Description:
The position of the patient when they took the medical test.

Ex:
- Standing
- Sitting
- Resting

Columns.Name: BodyLocationOfMedicalTest
Columns.Description:
The body location of the medical test.

Ex:
- Left arm

Columns.Name: Quantity
Columns.Description: The quantity associated with a test.

Columns.Name: NeverEventIndicator
Columns.Description: A Never Event is a serious, largely preventable, patient safety incident that should not occur. This field indicates whether the test is required as a result of such an event.

Columns.Name: RequirementTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Requirement Type.

Columns.Name: MedicalCareOrderId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Medical Care Order.

Columns.Name: FacilityFloorplanLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Facility Floorplan Location.

Columns.Name: MemberPreauthorizationCode
Columns.Description: The preauthorization code assigned to the member. The number stating that your treatment has been approved by your insurance plan.

Columns.Name: FacilityScheduledEventId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Facility Scheduled Event.

Columns.Name: MedicalTestNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding a Medical Test.
